Ad Text:
ACT - Hybrid working arrangement 
 12 + 12 month contract
 Decompose data & AI system requirements 

Our client, an independent statutory agency, who is responsible for measuring, reducing & offsetting carbon emission through regulation, require the services of an AI System Analyst.

Duties of the AI Systems Analyst

Elicit, analyse & document business, data & AI requirements translating to epics, features & user stories with testable acceptance criteria;
Define non-functional needs specific to AI (transparency, safety, robustness, latency, security, privacy);
Map processes/decision points to decide AI vs rules based & specify human authority levels & HITL checkpoints;
Co‑design evaluation frameworks for AI features (ground‑truth datasets, baselines; monitor performance, drift & fairness over time);
Partner with data scientists/engineers & product owners to turn outcomes into model objectives, features & data constraints;
Lead workshops, discovery and backlog refinement; produce service blueprints & future‑state workflows across teams.
Develop acceptance criteria and test cases for AI/ML features (shadow testing, A/B trials, red‑teaming, rollback plans);
Document prompt/model assumptions, guardrails and safety constraints (retrieval scope, prompt patterns, redaction).

Skills and Experience Required

 3+ years as a BA or Systems Analyst in digital or service delivery;
 Proven ability to write testable stories and acceptance criteria for AI features; and 
 Proficiency with Azure DevOps and Miro. 

How to Apply

For a copy of the full job description, including the application instructions, please get in touch with Daniel at Recruitment Hive by clicking the Quick Apply button.  Alternatively you can reach Daniel on (02) 6299 1006 to discuss further.

Please note that applications close on Wednesday the 1st of April 2026 at midday. Recruitment Hive welcome late applications to be considered for future opportunities.

